Preconditions:
The input array "sentences" must not be null.
The input array "sentences" must not be empty.
Each element in the input array "sentences" must be a non-null string.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the maximum number of words found in a single sentence.
The returned value should be greater than or equal to zero.
If all sentences in the input array are empty or contain no words, the method should return zero.
The method should not modify the input array "sentences".